Package com.redis.foundation.data

Class DataItem

java.lang.Object
com.redis.foundation.data.DataItem
public class DataItem extends Object
A data item captures a type, name, title, features, values and transient properties. Data items can be used to describe schema meta data and manage the serialization of data values. The Builder class can be used to quickly construct new data item instances.
Since:
1.0
Author:
Al Cole

    • addProperty

      public void addProperty(String aName, Object anObject)
      Add an application defined property to the data item.

      Notes:

      • The goal of the Dataitem is to strike a balance between providing enough properties to adequately model application related data without overloading it.
      • This method offers a mechanism to capture additional (application specific) properties that may be needed.
      • Properties added with this method are transient and will not be stored when saved.
      Parameters:
      aName - Property name (duplicates are not supported)
      anObject - Instance of an object
